article.headline: Spartans cruise in game after OT thriller
article.linkText: Michigan State breezes past Eastern Illinois
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Rene Haynes had 18 points and eight
rebounds in her first start this season to lead No. 12 Michigan
State to an 85-45 victory over Eastern Illinois on Thursday night.

Victoria Lucas-Perry had career highs of 15 points and seven
assists, and added eight rebounds as the Spartans (7-1) scored at
least 75 points for the seventh time in eight games. Megan Sparks
and Meagan Scaggs had 11 points apiece for the Panthers (3-3).

A week after an overtime win at then-No. 3 Notre Dame, Michigan
State held Eastern Illinois to 28.6-percent shooting, had a 44-8
edge in points inside and a 57-25 rebounding advantage that
included 27 offensive boards.

Kelli Roehrig became the 13th Spartan to score 1,000 career
points. She and Liz Shimek added 14 points apiece, and Big Ten
player of the week Lindsay Bowen had 10 points, six assists and a
career-high five steals.

With point guard Kristin Haynie out after spraining her left
thumb at practice Wednesday, Haynes scored 11 first-half points and
Shimek 10 to put the Spartans ahead 51-24 at the break.

Michigan State led 24-8, traded baskets for a few minutes, then
finished the half with a 16-5 spurt in its first home appearance in
six games.
